HEADWORD: Inoculum
<hw>In*oc"u*lum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Microbiology)</fld> <def>The preparation of microorganisms which
is inoculated{5} into a growth medium; <as>as, a small <ex>inoculum</ex>
may not work well for the production phase of a
fermentation</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
